---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Credits - FastQC">
  <h1>Credits</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Original FastQC</h2>
    <p>
      Written by <strong>Simon Andrews</strong> at
      <a href="https://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/">Babraham Bioinformatics</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC">github.com/s-andrews/FastQC</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Rust rewrite</h2>
    <p>
      By <strong>Phil Ewels</strong>
      (<a href="https://github.com/ewels">@ewels</a>).
      This rewrite was developed with the assistance of AI
      (<a href="https://claude.ai/claude-code">Claude Code</a> by Anthropic).
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/ewels/FastQC-Rust">github.com/ewels/FastQC-Rust</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Citation</h2>
    <p>
      If you use FastQC in your research, please cite the original project,
      not this rewrite. The analysis, algorithms, and scientific contribution
      are entirely the work of Simon Andrews.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>License</h2>
    <p>
      Both versions are licensed under the
      <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html">GNU General Public License v3.0</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Dependencies</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/clap">clap</a> &mdash; CLI argument parsing</li>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/noodles">noodles</a> &mdash; BAM/SAM reading</li>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/flate2">flate2</a> &mdash; gzip decompression</li>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/rayon">rayon</a> &mdash; parallel file processing</li>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/resvg">resvg</a> + <a href="https://crates.io/crates/tiny-skia">tiny-skia</a> &mdash; SVG to PNG rendering</li>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/statrs">statrs</a> &mdash; statistical distributions</li>
      <li><a href="https://crates.io/crates/hdf5-pure">hdf5-pure</a> &mdash; Fast5/HDF5 nanopore support</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem">
      Font: <a href="https://github.com/liberationfonts/liberation-fonts">Liberation Sans</a> (SIL Open Font License), bundled for consistent chart rendering.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
